    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*kantī-%i (%ikan%i + %iti%i). Для основы %ikan-%i в
        значении ‘молодой’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kanā-,
                    kanya-</w><gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>молодая женщина</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>kanistha-</w><gloss><q>младший</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>kainī-, kainyā-,</w></mentioned>
        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kanīz</w><gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa-x-dial"
        ><lang/><w>kīna</w><gloss><q>дочь</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Оформление %i-tī%i характерно
        для восточноиранских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>kōnd,
                    kənd</w><gloss><q>женщина</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>жена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w>kənd
                yund-</w><gloss><q>жениться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><w>be-kənd</w><gloss><q>вдовец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><w>vrit-kənd</w><gloss><q>жена брата</q></gloss></mentioned>, (? <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 547</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>kintika</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>knc</w><gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>247</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kant-(knt-)</w><gloss><q>род по женской
            линии</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref target="#ref_JA"
                /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1951, стр. 113—114</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"
                >1951, pp. 113—114</biblScope></bibl>). Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><lang/><w>-k’in</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>госпожа</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>знатная дама</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ЗВО"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">V 286 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">V 286 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). — Слово распознается в аланских фразах,
        записанных %sЦецом%s, в форме %iκιντζ%i ‘женщина’. Звуковая история ясна: %ikinʒ-%i из
        %i*kantī-%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lxincʼ"/> ‘узел’ из %i*granthi-%i. — Ср. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_kʼannæg"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                /><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                /><biblScope>II 478</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Фрейман,
                Rocznik orient. 1927, стр. 163</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Freiman, Rocznik
                orient. 1927, p. 163</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                /><biblScope>21-22</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>43, 119, 258, 316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*kantī-%i (%ikan%i + %iti%i). For the stem
        %ikan-%i in the meaning ‘young’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kanā-,
                    kanya-</w><gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>young woman</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>kanistha-</w><gloss><q>the youngest</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>kainī-, kainyā-,</w></mentioned>
        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kanīz</w><gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa-x-dial"
            ><lang/><w>kīna</w><gloss><q>daughter</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The %i-tī%i marking is
        typical of East Iranian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>kōnd,
                    kənd</w><gloss><q>woman</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>wife</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w>kənd
                yund-</w><gloss><q>get married</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><w>be-kənd</w><gloss><q>widower</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><w>vrit-kənd</w><gloss><q>brother's wife</q></gloss></mentioned>, (? <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 547</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>kintika</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>knc</w><gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>247</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kant-(knt-)</w><gloss><q>female line</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref target="#ref_JA"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru"
                >1951, стр. 113—114</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1951, pp.
                113—114</biblScope></bibl>). Cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><lang/><w>-k’in</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>mistress</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>lady of high degree</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ЗВО"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">V 286 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">V 286 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). — This word is recognized in Alan
        phrases recorded by %sTzetzes%s, in the form %iκιντζ%i ‘woman’. The phonetic history is
        clear: %ikinʒ-%i from %i*kantī-%i, as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lxincʼ"/> ‘knot’ from
        %i*granthi-%i. — Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼannæg"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 478</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Фрейман, Rocznik orient. 1927, стр.
                163</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Freiman, Rocznik orient. 1927, p.
                163</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                /><biblScope>21-22</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>43, 119, 258, 316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
